# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file — KataHarness
# Operator: taurran@gmail.com
# Created: 2026-06-30
#
# SUPPRESSION RATIONALE — python/PT (CWE-23 Path Traversal) in tools/kata_install.py
#
# Every python/PT LOW finding in this file is a false positive. _safe_abs() is the
# CWE-23 boundary guard: it rejects any path whose components include '..' via
#   any(part == ".." for part in p.parts)
# before resolving, and is called at every external-input entry point. Snyk's taint
# engine does not recognise this Python idiom as a sanitizer, so it marks downstream
# path operations (shutil.rmtree, shutil.copytree, Path / concatenation) as tainted.
# (Snyk's reported count varies with taint-propagation changes; the file-level ignore
# below is count-independent and blankets every python/PT finding in this file.)
#
# Additional constraint: several of these findings land inside the 5 byte-frozen engine
# fns (_link_or_copy, _flat_link_skills, install, copy_project, confirm_platform) that
# cannot receive inline # snyk:ignore comments without breaking the byte-freeze.
#
# Risk class: operator-controlled local CLI tool; all paths are operator-supplied and
# validated at the _safe_abs boundary. Residual risk is negligible.
# Severity: LOW (every python/PT finding here). No medium+ findings present.
#
# Risk accepted under Approach C (documented suppression). Review by: 2027-06-30.
version: v1.25.0
ignore:
  python/PT:
    - 'tools/kata_install.py':
        reason: >-
          FALSE POSITIVE: _safe_abs() rejects '..' traversal at every external-input
          boundary via `any(part == ".." for part in p.parts)` — Snyk's taint engine
          does not recognise this idiom as a sanitizer. Several findings are in the 5
          byte-frozen engine fns that cannot accept inline snyk:ignore comments.
          Operator-controlled local CLI; all paths are operator-supplied. Severity: LOW.
          File-level ignore is count-independent. Risk accepted per Approach C. Expiry: 2027-06-30.
        expires: '2027-06-30T00:00:00.000Z'
patch: {}
